headline: iShares Gold Trust (IAU) vs iShares Silver Trust (SLV): Which ETF Is a Better Investment?
summary: SLV has a higher expense ratio and lesser assets under management (AUM) than IAU.  SLV’s five-year risk and drawdown profile differs from IAU, reflecting the distinct volatility and risk profile of silver versus gold.  The key differences between iShares Silver Trust (NYSEMKT:SLV) and iShares Gold Trust (NYSEMKT:IAU) are cost, recent performance, and risk profile, with SLV carrying a higher expense ratio and more volatility, while IAU is larger and more affordable.

headline: Walmart Jumps to Nasdaq in Biggest Exchange Transfer on Record
summary: The Bentonville, Arkansas-based company, which has been on the NYSE since 1972, said it expects its shares to begin trading on the Nasdaq Global Select Market, the highest of the exchange’s three tiers, on Dec. 9.  The move to the tech-heavy Nasdaq reflects Walmart’s “technology-forward approach,” the retailer said, and it will transfer the listing of nine bonds to the exchange as well.  Large companies have made the move before, with PepsiCo Inc. abandoning its nearly century-long listing on the NYSE in 2017.
